SIMPLE: ultramontane
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ultramontane
<hw>Ul`tra*mon"tane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>ultramontanus</ets>; L. <ets>ultra</ets> beyond +
<ets>montanus</ets> belonging to a mountain, from <ets>mons</ets>,
<ets>montis</ets>, mountain: cf. F. <ets>ultramontain</ets>, It.
<ets>ultramontano</ets>. See <er>Ultra-</er>, and
<er>Mountain</er>.]</ety> <def>Being beyond the mountains; specifically,
being beyond the Alps, in respect to the one who speaks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This term was first applied, somewhat contemptuously, by
the Italians, to the nations north of the Alps, especially the Germans
and French, their painters, jurists, etc. At a later period, the French
and Germans applied it to the Italians. It is now more particularly used
in respect to religious matters; and <xex>ultramontane doctrines</xex>,
when spoken of north of the Alps, denote the extreme views of the pope's
rights and supremacy maintained by <persfn>Bellarmin</persfn> and other
Italian writers.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ultramontane</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ultramontane
<hw>Ul`tra*mon"tane</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who resides
beyond the mountains, especially beyond the Alps; a foreigner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who maintains extreme views favoring the pope's
supremacy. See <er>Ultramontanism</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ultramontanism</ent>⟦br⟧
